                                                                                                                                    Honda Motors Aviator takes off

              
	Honda Motorcycles Scooter India plans to sell up to one lakh units of the Aviator  a automatic scooter launched today  in 2008-09.
    
	The Aviators target customer is male. We plan to sell about one lakh Aviators in the next fiscal. Our overall sales target is around one million units, of which seven lakh will be scooters and three lakh motorcycles, N.K. Rattan, head of sales and marketing of HMSI, told reporters at the 9th Auto Expo in Delhi today. The Aviator is powered by a robust 102cc four-stroke engine, which generates 7BHP of power. 
    
	The body design is a combination of metal and high impact resistant ABS parts. 
    
	TATAS FIAT plan
    
	Tata Motors is planning to develop a few products jointly with Italian partner Fiat and sell vehicles in various countries.
       
	We are looking for something for some markets, Tata Motors managing director Ravi Kant told reporters here. He, however, did not elaborate, saying it was too premature to talk about it. Both the partners were working on different projects at the moment, he added.
    
	Tata Motors today launched variants of the multi-utility vehicle Sumo and the sedan Indigo. The new version 
    
	of the MUV  Sumo Grande  has been priced between Rs 6.55 lakh and Rs 7.49 lakh (ex-showroom, Delhi). However, the company is yet to announce the price for Indigo CS.
       
	HM offerings
    
	Hindustan Motors today unveiled three products, including an electronic car, in collaboration with Japans Mitsubishi Motors. The company launched a sport utility vehicle  Outlander  which will hit the roads in 6-8 months and will be priced at around Rs 20 lakh. 
                                                                       
